r is a 51 WARRIOR.  My cleric now 50, is my favorite, but I do know a thing or two about how it works.<P>I never once said meleeing is wrong, just that your idea of "Tanking" is looking from a different view.<P>To "TANK" is to taunt the mob(s) into hitting you, absorb the damage, deal what damage you can and keep the others safe from harm.  Tanks are often termed "Meat Sheild" because that is what they are, your sheild between the mob and group.<P>NOTE: This does NOT MEAN you will deal the most damage.  As a warrior I regularly stand there and watch rangers, rogues and monks dish out MUCH more damage than I.  But as long as the mob is munching my big barbarian rear, thats all that matters.  <P>If you love to melee (hitting the mob), by all means, do so.  Just be aware of the impact on your group.<P>Personally we have been romping in Chardok and I spend all my free time meditating, stunning gaters and HEALING.  <BR>Though when I spent 2 weeks in the City of Mist, I did one night of pulling. (We got bored and swapped rolls, shaman was pet caster, druid meleeing, cleric pulling, warrior bandaging, was pretty interesting to say the least.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/biggrin.gif">)<P>At a 'low level' meaning 20 or less, you will be able to deal melee damage well enough to contribute effectively.  So enjoy it now.<P>While one form of me is a 'pansy' elf, another is a big mean barbarian. And I wont quote Dennis Miller again, as the first time that obviously went over your head.<P>------------------<BR>~Calimayrn Anam'Cara<BR>50th Cleric of Tunare<BR>~Calizana Rhinelander<BR>Floating Barbarian Champion<BR><A HREF="http://www.lostorder.com" TARGET=_blank>Lost Order of Akalabeth</A><BR>Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fistandantylys</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">even without nuking i can beat most h2h<P>------------------<BR>i am fistandantylys disciple of mithaniel marr him