ty counts on you to stay alive so when you get into the upper levels it is your mana bar that is going to determine wether or not you are tanking. At low levels like you are at monsters don't hit for very much, but soon you will notice a BIG difference in MOB strength and in order to keep your group alive you need to sit med and heal. IF it is a good group you might find mana plentiful and you will DD monsters and go and tank a few for fun, but I will tell you this now; If you want to attack things and if you want to do the damage to monsters do not be a cleric. EQClerics are not designed for it. Be a paladin, it will give you a nice mix of warrior and cleric. And do not confuse soloing tactics with grouping tactics. I can still take out yellows and blues, and very very rarely a red but those are two different ball games. Clerics are very group dependant, the same as warriors, we need each other and we make each other better, and you are going to get more out of being a cleric if you concentrate on keeping everyone alive. At the level you are at now things are SO different, at higher levels it's only seconds between decisions that will either keep the group alive or kill everyone and if you are conentrating on tanking you make it that much harder to do your job cause it's not tanking, thats what the warriors are for.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fistandantylys</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i understand what yall are saying. i have a 59 cleric as well, a high elf i might add, im just saying that at the moment i am living proof that us clerics arent all weak and useless without alot of mana. oh and i was mainly talking about while soloing<P>------------------<BR>i am fistandantylys disciple of mithaniel marr himself i am hated by my hometown freeport but i think they just dont understand the mighty power of us clerics since most everywhere else ive been the people have enjoyed my compan